1. Interval Scheduling (Earliest Finish Time First)

âœ… Greedy Strategy

Pick the interval that finishes earliest among those that are compatible with the already chosen set.

ğŸ”’ Safety of the Strategy
	â€¢	Claim: There is always an optimal solution that includes the job with the earliest finishing time.
	â€¢	Proof (Exchange Argument):
	â€¢	Let I be the interval with the earliest finish time.
	â€¢	Take any optimal solution S.
	â€¢	If I \in S, weâ€™re done.
	â€¢	If I \notin S, then S must contain some other job J.
